Package controller

Class BSController

java.lang.Object
controller.BSController
public class BSController
extends java.lang.Object
The controller for the BSView. Not much to say here; it just responds to certain events and controls the model.
Version:
JDK 14.0.1
Author:
Matthew Ricci

  • Method Details

    • endGame

      public void endGame​(boolean iWin)
      Calls endGame() of BSModel. Invokes the endgame() method of BSModel.
      Parameters:
      iWin - a boolean that is true if you won, false if not.

    • initShipStates

      public void initShipStates()
      Tells the model to initialize ship states. Invokes the initShipStates() method of BSModel.

    • initGrid

      public void initGrid​(WhichGrid whichGrid)
      Tells the model to initialize one of the two grids. Tells the controller to initialize the grid, either yours or the other depending on what is passed in.
      Parameters:
      whichGrid - whether or not it's yours, or the other grid.

    • placeShip

      public void placeShip​(java.awt.Point point, Ship ship, Directions dir)
      Invokes the model to place a ship. Invokes the model to place a ship if it passed through the view's own checks. While you see a GUI it is backed by a 2d array of characters.
      Parameters:
      point - a Point object corresponding to the origin of that ship
      ship - the Ship you want to place on that Point
      dir - which direction the Ship is pointing - up or left.

    • placeShipOnOther

      public void placeShipOnOther​(java.awt.Point point, Ship ship, Directions dir)
      A testing oriented method that allows you to place a ship on the other grid. A testing oriented method that bypasses the GUI by allowing you to decide where the other player's ships should be.
      Parameters:
      point - a Point object corresponding to the origin of that ship
      ship - the Ship you want to place on that Point
      dir - which direction the Ship is pointing - up or left.

    • isGameOver

      public boolean isGameOver()
      Checks if the game is over. Invokes the model to check whether or not the game is over.
      Returns:
      true if the game is over, false if not.

    • makeMove

      public boolean makeMove​(java.awt.Point point, boolean myTurn)
      Tells the model that a move has been made. The method that handles clicking a spot to make a move. myTurn controls whose grid it's on.
      Parameters:
      point - the Point you want to make a hit at.
      myTurn - whose turn it is; if your turn, it goes on their grid. Otherwise, it goes on yours.
      Returns:
      true if the move was valid, false if not.

    • getMyGrid

      public char[][] getMyGrid()
      Testing oriented method, allows you to access model grid. A testing oriented method that allows direct access to the model's grid.
      Returns:
      model.grid your grid as stored in the model

    • getOtherGrid

      public char[][] getOtherGrid()
      Testing oriented method, allows you to access model other grid. A testing oriented method that allows direct access to the model's other grid.
      Returns:
      model.otherGrid their grid as stored in the model

    • updateTheirGrid

      public void updateTheirGrid​(char[][] newGrid)
      Set the model's other grid for testing purposes. A simple setter for the model's other grid. You just pass in the char[][] that you want it to be. Mostly a testing method.
      Parameters:
      newGrid - a char[][] corresponding to the other grid as stroed in the model.

    • getShipStates

      public Ship[] getShipStates()
      Access the ship states for testing purposes. A testing method that allows you to access the shipStates, since normally that is only access through the update() method of the BSView.
      Returns:
      model.shipStates a Ship[] of the current shipStates.
